{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-20T17:00:21.131Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Saying what to do instead of what not to do"},{"type":"text","text":" is a core principle of effective prompt engineering. Instead of just saying what not to do, tell the model explicitly what to do instead. This is rule #7 in OpenAI's official best practices guide."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": Models respond better to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"positive phrasing"},{"type":"text","text":" (\"Do this\") rather than "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"negative phrasing"},{"type":"text","text":" (\"Don't do that\")."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why This Works"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When you tell a model "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"what to do"},{"type":"text","text":", you give it a clear action to follow. When you tell it "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"what not to do"},{"type":"text","text":", you create ambiguity about what alternatives are available."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Research-backed principle"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Use positive phrasing ('Do this' instead of 'Don't do that')\" is one of the core rules for getting better AI results."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Models are trained to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"generate text"},{"type":"text","text":", not to avoid it. Saying \"don't write X\" is harder to follow than \"write Y instead.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Core Principle"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"❌ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Negative Phrasing (Bad)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"DO NOT ASK USERNAME OR PASSWORD."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Positive Phrasing (Good)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The agent will attempt to diagnose the problem and suggest a solution, whilst refraining from asking any questions related to PII.\nInstead of asking for PII, such as username or password, refer the user to the help article www.samplewebsite.com/help/faq"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The positive version tells the model "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"exactly what to do"},{"type":"text","text":" instead: refer the user to the help article."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Real Examples: Before & After"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 1: Customer Support Bot"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad (Negative):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"DO NOT ASK FOR USERNAME OR PASSWORD."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good (Positive):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instead of asking for PII, such as username or password, refer the user to the help article www.samplewebsite.com/help/faq"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The agent will attempt to diagnose the problem and suggest a solution, whilst refraining from asking any questions related to PII."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 2: Product Description Length"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad (Vague + Negative):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"The description for this product should be fairly short, a few sentences only, and not too much more.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good (Specific + Positive):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Use a 3 to 5 sentence paragraph to describe this product.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Be specific about the context, outcome, length, format, style, etc."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 3: Writing Style"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad (Negative):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Don't use technical jargon.\"\n\"Don't write in passive voice.\"\n\"Don't make it too long.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good (Positive):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Write for high schoolers using simple language.\"\n\"Use active voice.\"\n\"Keep it under 150 words.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Give clear instructions about what to do."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 4: Code Quality"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad (Negative):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Don't use external libraries.\"\n\"Don't invent APIs not in the codebase.\"\n\"Don't remove existing tests.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good (Positive):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Use only libraries already in the codebase.\"\n\"Follow existing patterns in the repo.\"\n\"Never remove or weaken existing tests.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Specify what to do with explicit constraints."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 5: Email Tone"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad (Negative):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Don't be too formal.\"\n\"Don't sound robotic.\"\n\"Don't use exclamation marks.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good (Positive):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Write a professional but friendly email.\"\n\"Use conversational language.\"\n\"Use a supportive, encouraging tone.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Define your target audience and use positive phrasing."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 6: Content Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad (Negative):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Summarize this text. Don't include every detail. Don't make it too long.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good (Positive):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Summarize the text below as a bullet point list of the most important points.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Be specific, descriptive, and as detailed as possible about the desired outcome, length, format, style."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 7: Entity Extraction"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad (Negative):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Extract the important entities mentioned in the text below. Don't forget company names. Don't skip people names.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good (Positive):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Extract the important entities mentioned in the text below.\nFirst extract all company names, then extract all people names, then extract specific topics which fit the content and finally extract general overarching themes.\n\nDesired format:\nCompany names: <comma_separated_list_of_company_names>\nPeople names: -||-\nSpecific topics: -||-\nGeneral themes: -||-\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Articulate the desired output format through examples. Show, and tell - the models respond better when shown specific format requirements."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Positive Phrasing Works Better"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Clear Action vs. Ambiguity"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Negative"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Don't write long paragraphs\" → What's the alternative?\n"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Positive"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Use short paragraphs (3-4 sentences each)\" → Clear action to follow"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Models Generate Text, Not Avoid It"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"LLMs are trained to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"generate text"},{"type":"text","text":", not to suppress it. Saying \"don't write X\" requires the model to inhibit its natural behavior. Saying \"write Y instead\" guides it toward a specific output."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Positive Framing Reduces Cognitive Load"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When you say \"don't do X,\" the model has to:\n1. Understand what X is\n2. Inhibit generating X\n3. Guess what to do instead"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When you say \"do Y,\" the model just needs to:\n1. Understand what Y is\n2. Generate Y"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Avoids Negative Bias"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Negative phrasing can create unintended bias. For example:\n- \"Don't be biased\" → Might cause the model to overcorrect\n- \"Be balanced and consider multiple perspectives\" → Clear guidance"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices for Positive Phrasing"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use \"Do This\" Instead of \"Don't Do That\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Don't use passive voice.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Use active voice.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use positive phrasing (\"Do this\" instead of \"Don't do that\")."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Replace \"Not\" with Specific Alternatives"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Don't make it too long.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Keep it under 150 words.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Be specific, descriptive and as detailed as possible about the desired context, outcome, length, format, style, etc."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Give Explicit Instructions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Write something about dogs.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"List 5 unique facts about Golden Retrievers, in bullet points.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Give clear instructions."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Specify What To Include"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Extract entities. Don't miss company names.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Extract the following 4 entity types: company names, people names, specific topics and themes.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Be specific about what to extract."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use Positive Constraints"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Don't use external libraries.\"\n\"Don't invent new APIs.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Use only libraries already in the codebase.\"\n\"Follow existing patterns in the repo.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Specify explicit constraints about what to do."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common Mistakes"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mistake 1: Overusing \"Don't\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Don't be too formal.\"\n\"Don't write long paragraphs.\"\n\"Don't use jargon.\"\n\"Don't make it too complex.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Be friendly and conversational.\"\n\"Use short paragraphs (3-4 sentences each).\"\n\"Use simple language suitable for high schoolers.\"\n\"Keep explanations clear and straightforward.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mistake 2: Vague Negative Instructions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Don't make it too long.\"\n\"Don't be too brief.\"\n\"Don't be too formal.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Keep it under 150 words.\"\n\"Write a 3-paragraph email.\"\n\"Use a professional but friendly tone.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mistake 3: Implied Negatives"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"❌ Bad:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Make sure it's not too complicated.\"\n\"Ensure it's not too simple.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"✅ Good:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Explain for a beginner in [field].\"\n\"Explain it to me like I'm 11 years old.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Say what to do, not what not to do"},{"type":"text","text":" is a core principle of effective prompt engineering:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": Models respond better to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"positive phrasing"},{"type":"text","text":" (\"Do this\") rather than "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"negative phrasing"},{"type":"text","text":" (\"Don't do that\")."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it works"},{"type":"text","text":":\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Clear action vs. ambiguity"},{"type":"text","text":" — Gives the model a specific action to follow\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Models generate text, not avoid it"},{"type":"text","text":" — LLMs are trained to generate text, not suppress it\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Reduces cognitive load"},{"type":"text","text":" — Model doesn't need to guess alternatives\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Avoids negative bias"},{"type":"text","text":" — Prevents overcorrection"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practices"},{"type":"text","text":":\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use \"Do this\" instead of \"Don't do that\""},{"type":"text","text":" — Positive phrasing\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Replace \"not\" with specific alternatives"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"Keep under 150 words\" vs. \"don't make it too long\"\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Give explicit instructions"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"List 5 facts\" vs. \"write something\"\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Specify what to include"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"Extract company names, people names, topics\" vs. \"don't miss names\"\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use positive constraints"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"Use only existing libraries\" vs. \"don't use external libraries\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instead of just saying what not to do, "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"say what to do instead"},{"type":"text","text":". This is rule #7 in OpenAI's official best practices guide and one of the most impactful techniques for improving prompt quality."}]}]}}
